<field>SCHEDULE.TYPE</field>
<desc>
            <p>Identifies the type of schedule allowed in the Payment Due module. </p>
            <p>Currently there are three types of schedules allowed but these may be further subdivided by the users to allow greater control if so desired. </p>
            <p>The three types that are allowed are: </p>
            <p>(a) RC  -  Rate Change (b) SC  -  Spread Change (c) CH  -  CHaser advice </p>
            <p>It is possible to define extra types of up to eight characters but the first two characters have to be one of the above allowable schedules. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>2-8 alphanumeric type A characters. (Mandatory input).</p>
            <p>First two characters must be one of the following:    RC, SC, CH.</p>
            <p>If the schedule type entered is greater than two characters then the first two characters must be one of the above types.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
